SIMPLE: rummager
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rummager
<hw>Rum"ma*ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
rummages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A person on shipboard whose
business was to take charge of stowing the cargo; -- formerly written
<altname>roomager</altname>, and <altname>romager</altname>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The master must provide a perfect mariner, called a
<qex>romager</qex>, to range and bestow all merchandise.</q>
<rj><qau>Hakluyt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rummer</ent>⟦br⟧
